-----------------------------------------
Plagiarism detection command line program
-----------------------------------------

I. Usage and Arguments
Example usage: 
	python plag_detect.py -syn synonyms_file -s source_file -r reference_file -n n_grams

-syn | --synonyms
	(required) specifies the file name for a list of synonyms

-s | --source
	(required) specifies the file name for the source file to be detected

-r | --reference
	(required) specifies the file name for the reference file

-n | --n_gram
	(optional) specifies the size of tuple. Default value is 3.

-h | --help
	(optional) print usage instructions

II. File list
------------
plag_detect.py					main program
plagiarism_detector.py 			plagiarism detection implementation
utils.py       					some utility functions
README						this file :)

III. System requirement
Python version >= 2.7

IV. Issues
a. Tokenize the input file.
b. Assume files could fit into memory.
